This is a patch file that renames a single enum constant in split/split.h from `RESET_COUNT` to `SPLIT_RESET_COUNT`. The change affects the metric tracking for keyboard split communication, specifically the counter that records reset events. Any code referencing the old name `RESET_COUNT` will need to be updated to use `SPLIT_RESET_COUNT` to maintain consistency, likely to avoid naming collisions or clarify that this metric is split-specific.